data.enText: if the value, amount or level of sth soars , it rises very quickly

data.chText: 猛增的成本；飞涨的物价；骤升的温度

data.enText: to rise quickly and smoothly up into the air
The rocket soared (up) into the air.
Her spirits soared (= she became very happy and excited) .
to fly very high in the air or remain high in the air

data.chText: 在山崖上空高高翱翔的鹰
data.enText: an eagle soaring high above the cliffs
to be very high or tall

data.chText: 在我们眼前，那座大楼巍然高耸。

data.enText: when music soars , it becomes higher or louder

ex.chText: 一只鸟从敞开的窗口飞了进来。
ex.enText: A bird flew in through the open window.

ex.chText: 别出声，要不然蝴蝶该飞走了。
ex.enText: Keep silent, or the butterfly will fly away.

ex.chText: 飞机在飞越这片海域时遭到了攻击。
ex.enText: The plane was attacked as it flew over the sea.

synonyms.bx: 泛指鸟或昆虫展开翅膀飞翔；也指飞机等在空中飞行。

ex.chText: 一只苍蝇在馒头上面飞来飞去。
ex.enText: A fly was hovering above a steamed bun.

ex.chText: 你看见在水面上方盘旋的那只鸟儿了吗？
ex.enText: Have you seen the bird hovering above the surface of the water?

ex.chText: 一架警用直升机悬停在头顶上空。

synonyms.bx: 指鸟、昆虫或直升机停留在某处上空。

ex.chText: 老鹰在山的上空高高翱翔。
ex.enText: The hawks are soaring high above the hills.

ex.chText: 那球腾空而起，飞到了右外场。
ex.enText: The ball soared to right field.

synonyms.bx: 指禽鸟高飞或某物从低处飞向高空。

tr: the act of rising upward into the air

example: The stock market soared after the cease-fire was announced

tr: fly a plane without an engine
fly upwards or high in the sky

example: the dollar soared against the yen

tr: fly by means of a hang glider

value.def: If the amount, value, level, or volume of something soars, it quickly increases by a great deal.

example.ex: Insurance claims are expected to soar...
example.tran: 预计保险索赔数量会急剧增加。

example.ex: Shares soared on the stock exchange...
...figures showed customer complaints had soared to record levels and profits were falling.
example.tran: 有数字表明，顾客投诉已经达到历史最高水平，利润正在下降。

example.ex: The temperature in the south will soar into the hundreds.
example.tran: 南方的温度会上升到一百多度。

value.tran: (数量、价值、水平、规模等)急升，猛涨

value.def: If something such as a bird soars into the air, it goes quickly up into the air.

example.ex: If you're lucky, a splendid golden eagle may soar into view...
example.tran: 幸运的话，会有一只光彩夺目的金雕飞入你的视野。

example.ex: Buzzards soar overhead at a great height...
The two sheets of flame clashed, soaring hundreds of feet high.
example.tran: 两片火焰化作一处，腾起了几百英尺高的烈焰。

value.def: Trees or buildings that soar upwards are very tall.

example.ex: ...the soaring spires of churches like St Peter's.
example.tran: 如圣彼得教堂一样高耸入云的尖塔

value.def: If music soars, it rises greatly in volume or pitch.

example.ex: The music soared to the rafters, carrying its listeners' hearts...
example.tran: 音乐响彻屋宇，震撼人心。

example.ex: His soaring voice cuts straight to the heart.
example.tran: 他那高昂的声音洞彻心扉。

value.tran: (音乐)音量猛地增大，音调陡然升高

value.def: If your spirits soar, you suddenly start to feel very happy.

example.ex: For the first time in months, my spirits soared.
example.tran: 几个月来，我的情绪第一次高涨起来。
